OK, I can reproduce your problem here, and there&#39;s actually another old 
issue describing it:

http://webteam.archive.org/jira/browse/HER-540

At the Internet Archive, we actually don&#39;t do any crawls or testing of 
Heritrix under Windows. Our official target platform is Linux, though we 
try to retain operability on Windows, Mac, and other Java-capable 
platforms when informed of issues. I suppose any active Heritrix 1.14 
users on Windows have already worked around this, perhaps simply because 
they reuse their own custom profiles/jobs rather than the default.

A suitable workaround is to unpack the &#39;profiles/default&#39; directory from 
the heritrix-1.14.0.jar file into your Heritrix install directory at 
&#39;conf/profiles/default&#39;. Then, restart Heritrix, and it will get the 
proper unpacked default profile.

(The .JAR file is just a ZIP file; you can make a copy of it, rename it 
to end with .ZIP, and then the Windows zip file support will let you 
look inside and copy out the &#39;profiles/default&#39; directory, or extract 
the entire contents.)

I hope this helps and sorry for the initial confusion about what was 
causing your problems.

- Gordon @ IA





